long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
Cunny Translate lets you easily translate to and from Cunny Code, a variation of Morse Code, while browsing the web.

Its functionality is fairly straightforward:
1. Select/highlight Cunny Code or regular texts with your cursor.
2. Click the extension icon or right click and choose "Cunny Translate" from the context menu.
3. The popup window for the extension should open and automatically translate Cunny Code to English and vice versa.

Cunny Translate also offers the ability to encrypt and decrypt messages with a password for those that want to keep their communications private.

Learn more about Cunny Code at https://sethclydesdale.github.io/cunny-code/code/

You can also contribute to the development of this extension on GitHub at https://github.com/SethClydesdale/cunny-translate
